//Tendons - Quadriceps tendon

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 08 - Soft parts of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Tendons - Quadriceps tendon' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Tear' checkbox is enabled
And 'Enthesiopathy' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Tear' checkbox
Then 'Complete tear' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial tear' radio button is enabled
And 'Intramuscular' radio button is enabled
And 'Intratendinous' radio button is enabled
And 'Insertion' radio button is enabled
And 'Retraction' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Partial tear' radio button
Then 'Rectus femoris muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Vastus medialis muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Vastus lateralis muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Vastus intermedius muscle' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Insertion' radio button
Then 'Avulsion Patella' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Retraction' radio button
Then 'Dimension' input field is enabled
And 'Haematoma suprapatellar' is enabled
And 'Bone bruise' checkbox is enabled
And 'Haemarthros' checkbox is enabled
And 'Patella baja' checkbox is enabled
And 'Joint effusion' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Enthesiopathy' checkbox
Then 'Thickening/Edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bursitis suprapatellaris' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone marrow edema upper patellar pole' checkbox is enabled
And 'Muscular atrophy' checkbox is enabled
And 'Intratendinal calcification' checkbox is enabled
And 'Traction spur' checkbox is enabled